I have a new recipe so easy that is almost not even a recipe! Yet this parsley root salad is incredibly good. The secret? Parsley root is actually so delicious on its own that I quite often eat it like a snack without any dressing. And it is a perfect winter veggie, packed with Vitamin C and minerals.
To make this salad I added balsamic vinegar, olive oil, salt & pepper, and some herbs.

Sprouted Lentil Salad with Leek and Purslane

Sprouting seeds and legumes transforms them from food to superfood.
When sprouted, seeds and legumes provide a highly concentrated source of predigested vitamins, minerals, amino acids, fatty acids, and chlorophyll. The germination enhance the quality of the nutrients.

It's definitely worth to try it! Check my latest recipe on wwww.parsleyandcilantro.com

#sprouts #vegan #superfood #healthyfood #beautifulfood

No-knead Focaccia

I am still having fun with my no-knead dough. Although I have a kneading machine I like to make my bread with this procedure. I think it's fascinating to see how with no effort I can obtain such an amazing baked product! 
And tomato is not the only topping that goes great with it. Try to top the focaccia with broccoli instead!
